column4: Problem Solving – PRB2 Gathering evidence – Students will gather and analyze credible evidence in order to determine its validity for application to a problem.
column11: Advanced: Evidence is gathered and comprehensively evaluated to determine its application to a problem
column13: Proficient: Evidence is gathered and competently evaluated to determine its application to a problem
column15: Progressing: Evidence is gathered, but not enough to competently evaluate its application to a problem
column17: Beginning: Evidence is gathered, but lacks sufficient quality or evaluation of its application to a problem
column19: Unsatisfactory: No evidence is gathered or there is no attempt to evaluate its application to a problem
